<TITLE> Chad says over 60 followers of `holy man' killed </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 N'DJAMENA, Wed Jul 2, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Chad's security forces killed 63 disciples of a Muslim spiritual leader in a weekend assault against his base after he had threatened to launch a holy war, Security Minister Ahmat Mahamat Bachir said on Wednesday. The government had said on Tuesday that 12 extremists and two members of the security forces were killed in Sunday's operation at Kouno, 300 km (185 miles) southeast of N'Djamena. Giving an updated toll to journalists on Wednesday, Bachir said 63 followers of Ahmat Ismael Bichara and four members of the security forces died in the operation
